Preference Signal Engine v1.0

Identity extraction, narrative inference, prediction, and value exchange in one system

Core thesis

People do not merely choose things. They reveal themselves through them.

A favorite dog, team, song, brand, or hobby is usually a compressed signal containing:
	•	memory
	•	emotion
	•	reinforcement
	•	identity
	•	narrative fit
	•	current context

So the real object is not the product.
The real object is the person-structure underneath the preference.

That gives us a system:

Observe choices → extract latent identity → model narrative fit → predict future affinities → generate aligned recommendations → convert stable patterns into portable value

⸻

1. One-line definition

Preference Signal Engine = a system that converts choices into an evolving identity vector, modulates it through runtime context, infers narrative structure, and uses the result for prediction, matching, personalization, self-discovery, and value exchange.

⸻

2. Canonical model

Base equation

P = f(O, R, I, N, E)

Where:
	•	O = Origin
First imprint, early exposure, family inheritance, emotional anchor
	•	R = Reinforcement
Repetition, reward, group validation, habit loops
	•	I = Identity
Traits the person experiences or wishes to express
	•	N = Narrative
Internal myth: underdog, protector, rebel, builder, sovereign, romantic, outsider, healer
	•	E = Environment
The present context that changes what gets expressed

This means a preference is not static. It is an expression event.

