Layer 2: Decomposition Layer

Breaks each choice into interpretable causes.

For every preference event, estimate:
	•	Origin score
	•	Reinforcement score
	•	Identity score
	•	Narrative score
	•	Environment score

Example

Preference: “I love German shepherds”

Possible decomposition:
	•	Origin: childhood dog
	•	Reinforcement: repeated good experiences
	•	Identity: respect for discipline, intelligence, protectiveness
	•	Narrative: guardian/protector archetype
	•	Environment: desire for security or structure

So the surface preference becomes a structured object.

