Layer 5: Runtime Expression Layer

This is the epigenetic switchboard.

The person is not identical in every context.
Their base pattern exists, but its expression changes.

Runtime equation

expressed_state = f(base_state, environment, constraints, history)

Or more concretely:

preference_output = IV × context_multiplier × governance_gate × safety_gate

Environmental switches
	•	alone vs group
	•	work vs leisure
	•	morning vs late night
	•	stressed vs calm
	•	scarcity vs abundance
	•	public vs private
	•	dating vs friendship
	•	high-status setting vs relaxed setting

Construct-controlled switches
	•	exploration mode
	•	comfort mode
	•	disciplined mode
	•	expert mode
	•	playful mode
	•	high-safety mode
	•	shared-coherence mode

So someone may have:
	•	base love for wild, intense aesthetics
	•	but express minimalism in professional contexts
	•	and nostalgia in intimate contexts

This prevents the system from mistaking momentary expression for total identity.

