Layer 6: Prediction Engine

Uses the evolving IV and runtime switches to estimate likely future preference.

Predictive tasks
	•	next item preference
	•	compatibility with another user
	•	conversion likelihood
	•	taste drift over time
	•	category expansion path
	•	ideal recommendation order
	•	likely rejection reasons
	•	identity-consistent purchases
	•	phase/state transitions

Example outputs
	•	“You are likely to prefer rugged-trustworthy brands over sleek-luxury brands.”
	•	“Your late-night music taste shifts toward melancholy intimacy.”
	•	“You may not want the most popular dog breed; you want a breed that feels competent, loyal, and symbolically serious.”

