Layer 8: Exchange Layer

Converts stable, validated signal into portable value.

This is where it plugs into your broader meaning economy.

Units
	•	Signal Units (SU): raw behavioral contributions
	•	Invariant Credit (IC): validated, cross-context traits or preferences that remain stable enough to be reused

SU examples
	•	100 pairwise choices
	•	23 repeated category preferences
	•	17 strong consistency events
	•	4 reversal events with explanation

IC examples
	•	stable preference for trust/loyalty-coded aesthetics
	•	strong underdog affinity across sports, media, and brands
	•	consistent protector archetype activation
	•	validated preference for rugged-functional over decorative-luxury

The difference:
	•	SU is raw
	•	IC is distilled

That makes IC portable across apps and domains.

