7. Scoring logic

Pairwise update rule

Each choice updates both item scores and latent trait scores.

Simplified:

Δtrait = learning_rate × confidence × context_weight × signal_strength

Where signal_strength depends on:
	•	decisiveness
	•	response speed
	•	consistency with prior pattern
	•	emotional salience
	•	explanation richness

Identity vector update

IV(t+1) = IV(t) + Σ(weighted_event_contributions) - drift_penalty + reinforcement_bonus

Narrative scoring

Map choices onto archetype likelihoods:

NarrativeScore(archetype) = Σ(item_tags × consistency × context_fit)

Invariant promotion rule

A pattern gets promoted from provisional to IC only if it is:
	•	repeated
	•	cross-context stable
	•	cross-category stable
	•	not contradicted too heavily
	•	interpretable

So:
	•	liking one rugged boot is not enough
	•	repeatedly choosing loyalty/protection/utility-coded things across dogs, characters, clothing, and teams probably is

