9. Why this beats normal recommenders

Normal recommendation systems mostly do:
	•	co-click
	•	collaborative filtering
	•	content similarity
	•	session optimization

Those are shallow.

This system adds:
	•	identity extraction
	•	symbolic tagging
	•	narrative inference
	•	runtime modulation
	•	invariant distillation
	•	cross-domain portability

So instead of just knowing:

you clicked boots

it learns:

you are drawn to earned competence and protective seriousness, especially under low-social-pressure conditions

That is a much higher-value signal.

