11. Governance

This part matters.

Without governance, this becomes manipulative.
With governance, it becomes empowering.

Core invariants
	•	user can inspect their vector
	•	user can correct the model
	•	recommendations should be reversible
	•	no hidden coercive steering
	•	portable data requires explicit consent
	•	high-confidence identity claims must be explainable
	•	sensitive inference categories should be tightly limited
	•	user must be able to reset or fork profiles

Safe framing

The engine should help users:
	•	discover themselves
	•	organize their preferences
	•	make better choices
	•	receive better-fit recommendations

Not:
	•	trap them in a narrow identity
	•	exploit insecurity
	•	intensify unhealthy loops
	•	manipulate them without visibility

