20. Clean repo-ready abstraction

Abstract

Preference Signal Engine v1.0 is a behavioral inference system that treats user choices as compressed signals of identity, memory, narrative, and context. It captures pairwise and ranked preferences, decomposes them into latent features, updates an evolving identity vector, modulates expression through runtime context, infers narrative structure, and uses the result for prediction, matching, reflection, and portable value exchange. The system transforms raw preference events into higher-order invariants that can be surfaced to the user or reused across applications with consent.

